Package nusri.fyp.demo.entity

Class StateMachineLog

java.lang.Object
nusri.fyp.demo.entity.StateMachineLog
@Entity public class StateMachineLog extends Object
StateMachineLog entity class that records the execution flow of the state machine.
This includes the user identifier, associated preset, start and end times, and observation data stored by timestamp (action recognition information).

    getMatchingPresetNodes()
    Retrieves the matching PresetNode objects based on the observations.
    The method returns a map of timestamps to the corresponding PresetNode objects.
    A matching logic is applied where the AbstractActionObservation.s() method's result is checked against the actions in the PresetNode list.
    The match is considered if the action from the observation matches the action in the node either as a prefix or suffix, or exactly.

    • getMatchingPresetNodes

      public Map<Long,List<PresetNode>> getMatchingPresetNodes()
      Retrieves the matching PresetNode objects based on the observations.
      The method returns a map of timestamps to the corresponding PresetNode objects.
      A matching logic is applied where the AbstractActionObservation.s() method's result is checked against the actions in the PresetNode list.
      The match is considered if the action from the observation matches the action in the node either as a prefix or suffix, or exactly.
      Returns:
      A map of timestamps and corresponding matching PresetNode objects.

    • getMatchingPresetNodes

      public Map<Long,List<PresetNode>> getMatchingPresetNodes(boolean addTransfer)
      Retrieves the matching PresetNode objects based on the observations.
      The method returns a map of timestamps to the corresponding PresetNode objects.
      The match logic follows the same as getMatchingPresetNodes(), but with an option to add a "transfer" action if no observations exist.
      A matching logic is applied where the AbstractActionObservation.s() method's result is checked against the actions in the PresetNode list.
      The match is considered if the action from the observation matches the action in the node either as a prefix or suffix, or exactly.
      Parameters:
      addTransfer - If true, adds a "transfer" action observation if no observations are present.
      Returns:
      A map of timestamps and corresponding matching PresetNode objects.

      Retrieves the matching PresetNode IDs for each timestamp.

    • generateAllNodeChains

      public List<List<PresetNode>> generateAllNodeChains(List<PresetNode> presetNodes)
      Generates all possible chains of PresetNodes.
      This method calculates every possible permutation of the provided PresetNode list.
      The permutations represent all possible step sequences for the state machine based on the given preset.
      Parameters:
      presetNodes - A list of all PresetNodes.
      Returns:
      A list of all possible chains (permutations) of PresetNodes.

    • getDuration

      Returns the duration of the entire process from the first observation to the last.

      The duration of the process in milliseconds. If no data exists, returns 0.
